Renders `docs/STATUS.md` — a human-readable Markdown table of tasks, sorted by impact (high to low) then difficulty (easy to hard) — from the canonical `docs/status.json` store. This is a pure function: same store always produces identical bytes, so the view never drifts from disk.

The rendered output delegates row formatting to `ctx_core::status_table::render_row`, which must produce Markdown table syntax compatible with the fixed header. Task IDs are omitted from the table; they surface only in `ctx-status list` to keep the 4-column shape aligned with `ctx-brief`.

`render_markdown(store: &Store) -> String` builds the full document: HEADER constant (stating source of truth and sort order) followed by each sorted task's rendered row. The function is deterministic and idempotent — appending a task appends only that task's line, leaving prior content unchanged.